🧚🏻‍♂️ Domestic Goddess... NOT! 🙅🏻‍♀️
.⁠
Cooking and cleaning takes up so much time... And I seem to always take more than the prescribed! 🤦🏻‍♀️ Recipes that indicate 'Preparation Time: 20mins, Cooking Time: 20mins' usually have me starting in the kitchen at 4PM and serving just-in-time at 7.30pm. HOW DO WORKING PARENTS DO THIS??? 🤷🏻‍♀️👏🏻😱 #RESPECT⁠
.⁠
On my CB list is 'Bake/Cook once a week' 👩🏻‍🍳🍳🍰 I'm flat out by Saturday night from cooking ONE MEAL. Now I know what Hercules feels like with his Twelve Labours 🥒 Slaying the nine-headed Hydra is like me cutting onions... seemingly never ending and makes me cry 😅⁠
.⁠
🍴What DOES make me continue is seeing a physical outcome AND pottering together around the kitchen with @VincentCheokBC 🍝 So far, we've made baked salmon, (a lot of) minestrone soup and KFC chicken rice 🥞🍲🍚⁠
.⁠
What beginner level recipes reap big yummy taste results for you? I would prefer not to spend half my weekend being domestic 🧹🧼😆⁠
.
PS: Sharing my banana choc chip baking in my Stories!

.⁠
.⁠

My daughters have taken over the cooking... which is great... but I obviously have never taught them how to clean the kitchen, so that still down to me! Can't complain ... lovely to be spending so much time with them!!!

Ooh girl! Check out the link in my bio I have a cookbook for under $10 you’ll love! 7 recipes that are a cinch to make - plus creates leftovers so you don’t have to cook everynight! - coming from the mom of 3 who works full time! Ingot you girl! 👊🏼
@soljinutrition Hi Viktoria, my latest banana bread kinda-fail is on Stories! 🙈 Would love your wisdom, if you’ve any idea what happened!
Oh yum! I'll have to check out your stories!

@scenesfromnadine Phew, so glad someone else is experiencing the same thing, Nadine! 😅Or maybe that they can chop with masterchef-type speed? I don’t know, it’s a gross underestimation of time by my standards 🙈

Same here! I think those recipe blogs that say that prep time is '5 minutes' or '10 minutes' actually mean that they probably prepared the night before or something! I always take forever in the kitchen!
@msmariatan Love cod fish but never tried cooking it myself! So I should buy miso soup paste for this, correct, Marie?
@positiveleepeilin miso paste but not miso soup paste. There are different types of miso. Buy the one that says shiro miso or saikyo miso. I bought mine from ntuc. Will message you the detail! :)
@msmariatan Hahaha, I would definitely have put miso soup paste on top, if not for your clarification, Marie 🙈

Cod / salmon miso (depending if you prefer white/red fish). You just need to marinade the fish for 1-2 days, then put it in the oven for 20 minutes then that's it! To make the marinade is also very easy. You only need to buy miso paste and mirin. Plus sugar and salt but I'm sure you already have them in your kitchen :)
